The paper deals with the problem of polar coding for multiple access channels, which is a topic in information theory and communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and computational complexity analysis, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the achievable rates and resolution of the uniform rate region, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
